p: In contrast to imported CHIKV cases, the monthly number of overseas arrivals exhibited a linear increased trend during the study period ( Fig 5A). There was also a strong component of seasonality. For the monthly overseas arrivals, the strongest positive seasonal effects occurred in each January, followed by October, July, April and December, while the strongest negative seasonal effects were observed in each June, followed by February, May, August, November, March and September ( Fig 5B).
